{"id":"quant-ph/0508033","submitter":"Hiroto Kubotani","authors":"Hiroto Kubotani, Mikito Toda, Satoshi Adachi","title":"Universality in Dynamical Formation of Entanglement for Quantum Chaos","comments":"4 pages, 5 figures; submitted to Phys. Rev. Lett","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.74.032314","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  Dynamical formation of entanglement is studied for quantum chaotic\nbi-particle systems. We find that statistical properties of the Schmidt\neigenvalues for strong chaos are well described by the random matrix theory of\nthe Laguerre ensemble. This implies that entanglement formation for quantum\nchaos has universal properties, and does not depend on specific aspects of the\nsystems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2005 14:36:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
